race.comment: The $300,000 Group 3 BJ McLachlan Stakes. TORNADO VALLEY (1) broke through for a G3 win at Flemington last time out and winning rider Brown follows him up the coast here. Tuned up for this with a recent trial victory and should be going very close again. ZIP LOCK (3) was in the betting when facing the starter for the first time and didn't let supporters down with a solid Doomben victory. Sure to have come on with that run now under the belt and can make his presence felt again. REMEMBRALL (7) looked handy saluting at Doomben on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Can return a winner. MAGRITTE (6) has hit the frame in all three career outings and looks to be knocking on the door of a maiden victory. In the mix. FEARLESS WIN (10) next best in a race with only a handful of chances.
